{
    "name": "Fading Fox",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any temperate land<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary or pair<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Fade Away (Ex)</b> Fading foxes take their name from their uncanny ability to change their coloration. As a standard action, a fading fox can alter the coloration of its pelt, allowing it to attempt Stealth checks without cover or concealment, even while being observed. It can use this ability only in natural settings."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "\u201cSmarter than my own children,\u201d is the common refrain from those nobles who\u2019ve pitted their hunting skills against the fading fox. Agile, alert, and clever, these handsome beasts find few traps or enclosures they can\u2019t escape\u2014and few gardens or larders they can\u2019t enter. To aristocratic hunters, they represent the ultimate quarry to track, leaving no footprints, running confusing trails, and easily vanishing from sight, but to the common people of western Taldor, fading foxes have become a surprisingly common and persistent pests they have neither the ability nor the permission to trap."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This regal fox\u2019s coat shifts subtly between silver, red, and dull brown as it walks.</i>",
